{
  "local_port": 44716,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I make best Szechuan noodles?",
  "response": "Making Szechuan noodles is a delightful culinary experience. Here's a step-by-step guide to prepare a delicious and authentic version of this spicy dish:\n\n### Ingredients:\n- **Noodles:** 200g dried Chinese egg noodles or any preferred type\n- **Vegetable oil:** 2 tablespoons\n- **Garlic:** 4 cloves, minced\n- **Ginger:** 1 tablespoon, grated\n- **Szechuan peppercorns:** 1 teaspoon\n- **Dried red chilies:** 4-5, chopped (adjust to taste)\n- **Vegetables:** 1 bell pepper (sliced), 1 carrot (julienned), and 1 cup of snap peas\n- **Scallions:** 3, chopped\n- **Proteins (optional):** Chicken breast (sliced), shrimp, or tofu\n- **Soy sauce:** 3 tablespoons\n- **Rice vinegar:** 2 tablespoons\n- **Hoisin sauce:** 2 tablespoons\n- **Chili paste:** 1 tablespoon (or more depending on taste)\n- **Sesame oil:** 1 tablespoon\n- **Sugar:** 1 teaspoon\n- **Broth or water:** \u00bc cup\n\n### Instructions:\n\n#### 1. **Preparation:**\nStart by preparing all your ingredients. Mince the garlic, grate the ginger, chop the vegetables and scallions, and slice the proteins if using.\n\n#### 2. **Cook the noodles:**\nBoil the noodles according to the package directions. Once cooked, drain and rinse under cold water to stop the cooking process. Set aside.\n\n#### 3. **Infuse the oil:**\nHeat the vegetable oil in a large pan or wok over medium heat. Add the Szechuan peppercorns and stir-fry for a minute or until fragrant. Remove and discard the peppercorns, leaving the infused oil.\n\n#### 4. **Stir-fry aromatics:**\nIncrease the heat to medium-high. In the infused oil, add the garlic, ginger, and dried red chilies. Stir-fry for a minute, ensuring they don\u2019t burn.\n\n#### 5. **Cook the protein:**\nIf using any proteins, add them now and stir-fry until fully cooked. Remove from pan and set aside.\n\n#### 6. **Stir-fry vegetables:**\nAdd the bell pepper, carrot, and snap peas to the pan. Stir-fry until tender-crisp, about 3-4 minutes.\n\n#### 7. **Make the sauce:**\nIn the same pan, add soy sauce, rice vinegar, hoisin sauce, chili paste, sesame oil, and sugar. Stir to combine and cook for a minute.\n\n#### 8. **Combine everything:**\nAdd the cooked noodles and proteins (if using) back into the pan. Pour in the broth or water to loosen the noodles and mix everything well until the noodles are coated with the sauce and heated through.\n\n#### 9. **Finish with scallions:**\nAdd the chopped scallions and stir for an additional minute.\n\n### Garnish and Serving:\nServe your Szechuan noodles hot, garnished with some extra chopped scallions if desired. You can also add crushed peanuts or sesame seeds for extra texture and flavor.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Adjust spice levels:** The amount of dried chilies and chili paste can be adjusted according to your heat preference.\n- **Protein flexibility:** Feel free to use any protein of your choice, or omit it for a vegetarian version.\n- **Authenticity:** For an authentic touch, use Chinese black vinegar instead of rice vinegar if available.\n\nEnjoy your homemade Szechuan noodles, bursting with bold flavors and delightful spices!",
